It was given to him so PR4Y could put it back up, he didn’t want it to be released. He also released v4 on accident, you make it sound like he posted a download URL.

Err no. He specifically told PR4Y he could do whatever he wanted with it (more specifically use it to create MidiEvo - which failed). He did not care about putting the actual server back up (he would’ve given the source to Ruckus or Kossu if he really wanted that).

If that’s the case like i said remove every source RELEASE but xENT since he released his own?

Releasing a WAY more stable demonik/divine src then already out for people to use is ALOT of help in the “development” community.
